blogs.title: Web dev top tips
blogs.body: Amazon Simple Queue Service (SQS) is a fully managed message queuing service provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS). It allows decoupling the components of a cloud application so they can run independently, increasing the overall fault tolerance and scalability of the application. SQS acts as a buffer between the application components, temporarily storing messages as they travel between them.
